00:46.588 --> 00:50.259
Did you think we were
gonna be together forever?

00:54.805 --> 00:58.392
You know, you act
like such a little kid.

00:58.475 --> 01:02.521
Like, you're a little eight-year-old
runnin' around, bein' goofy.

01:02.604 --> 01:05.816
You know, I just
can't stand it anymore.

01:05.899 --> 01:07.901
What do you want me to say?

01:07.985 --> 01:10.445
Don't say nothin'.

01:10.529 --> 01:12.823
Can I say I'm sorry?

01:12.906 --> 01:16.451
It's too late.
Just don't say nothin'.

01:17.744 --> 01:20.163
Can I kiss you one last time?

01:23.959 --> 01:27.963
Tell me.
Tell me that you love me.

01:31.925 --> 01:33.844
Do you love me?

01:56.533 --> 01:58.452
They used to get around,

01:58.535 --> 02:01.330
walkin'around, lookin'at stuff.

02:10.214 --> 02:14.134
They used to try to find clues
to all the mysteries...

02:14.218 --> 02:17.179
and mistakes God had made.

02:44.081 --> 02:49.336
My friend George said that he
was gonna live to be 100 years old.

02:49.419 --> 02:55.175
"He said"... "He said that he was gonna be"
the president of the United States.

02:56.969 --> 03:02.140
I wanted to see him lead a parade
and wave a flag on the Fourth ofJuly.

03:02.224 --> 03:04.393
He just wanted greatness.

03:11.483 --> 03:13.735
The grown-ups in my town,

03:13.777 --> 03:16.780
they were never kids
like me and my friends.

03:20.826 --> 03:24.580
They had worked in wars
and built machines.

03:24.621 --> 03:27.583
It was hard for them
to find their peace.

03:30.627 --> 03:33.046
Don't you know how that feels?

04:34.358 --> 04:37.903
I like to go to beautiful places...

04:37.986 --> 04:41.281
where there's waterfalls
and empty fields.

04:41.365 --> 04:45.661
Just places that are nice
and calm and quiet.

04:54.002 --> 04:56.755
Come back here!

04:56.839 --> 04:58.882
You will not defeat me!

05:04.513 --> 05:07.766
- Hi, George.
- Hi.

05:07.850 --> 05:10.894
- What you doin'?
- Nothin'.

05:14.356 --> 05:18.944
You will die in the graveyard of...
You know what I mean.

05:19.027 --> 05:21.697
'Cause I am smooth!

05:27.786 --> 05:31.373
- Who's cat is that?
- This is Nancy the cat.

05:31.456 --> 05:35.127
I'm baby-sittin' her for my cousin.

05:35.210 --> 05:37.546
She's in Florida somewhere.

05:37.629 --> 05:41.550
So, why aren't you over there
with Vernon and them?

05:41.592 --> 05:43.594
My head hurts.

05:43.635 --> 05:46.013
Yeah, my legs hurt.

05:48.640 --> 05:52.394
I love you!
I love you!

05:52.436 --> 05:56.648
This is war!

06:00.110 --> 06:04.406
When I look at
my friends, I know there's goodness.

06:04.448 --> 06:08.869
I can look at their feet,
or when I hold their hands,

06:08.952 --> 06:11.914
I pretend I can see the bones inside.

06:41.318 --> 06:45.322
This place is falling apart
faster than we can do anything.

06:45.405 --> 06:48.408
You're supposed
to be a leader, Damascus.

06:48.492 --> 06:54.164
You oughta look around
and see the hazards.

06:54.248 --> 06:57.292
I'm holding you for a day's pay.

06:57.376 --> 07:00.337
You're holding me
for a day's pay? A day's pay?

07:00.379 --> 07:03.090
End of discussion.
I've got a train yard to run.

07:03.173 --> 07:06.093
That's what I'm talkin' about.
I'm talkin' about conditions.

07:06.176 --> 07:09.221
I'm talkin' about goin' home every
night and not coughing up blood.

07:09.304 --> 07:11.849
I'm talkin' about I got burns
on the back of my neck.

07:11.932 --> 07:15.060
I'm talkin' about animals
runnin' up, tearin' up track.

07:15.143 --> 07:20.482
What am I 'posed to do when
one of those dogs bite me, huh?

07:20.524 --> 07:23.986
Your workman's compensation
doesn't cover that, does it?

07:25.612 --> 07:28.323
Think about it,
Damascus. You're a good worker.

07:28.365 --> 07:31.910
Don't do anything you're gonna
regret six months from now.

07:35.622 --> 07:38.250
I'm thinkin' about it.

08:03.066 --> 08:05.360
The first time George
saw his dog,

08:05.444 --> 08:08.197
it was sittin'in some feces.

08:10.908 --> 08:14.828
It didn't have anywhere to go,
no one to love it.

08:17.581 --> 08:20.709
It couldn't do no harm but walk.

08:31.887 --> 08:34.847
Ears are nasty,
his head is nasty,

08:34.932 --> 08:38.309
his legs are nasty,
his tail's crooked.

08:38.393 --> 08:43.607
Get off me, man!
You play too much.

09:18.809 --> 09:23.772
Hey, Augie, now that Damascus quit,
I bet my dad makes you supervisor.

09:23.856 --> 09:27.651
- Yeah, wouldn't that be fun?
- Maybe you'll get a raise.
Hey, could I get a light?

09:27.734 --> 09:32.447
I am absolutely disgusted with
all of you. Completely disgusted.

09:32.489 --> 09:36.326
Look at what you eat for lunch.
Look at that. What is that?
That's preservatives.

09:36.410 --> 09:39.121
- "It's fudge."
- "Euless."

09:39.162 --> 09:41.748
- Nobody cares what you're saying.
- It causes cancer.

09:41.832 --> 09:44.793
- You're gay.
- I'm not gay. I have a wife, okay?

09:44.835 --> 09:47.796
It causes cancer. At least, if you're
gonna eat that, have some almonds.

09:47.838 --> 09:50.716
How do you deal with yourself?
When I go to the bathroom,

09:50.799 --> 09:52.718
I like to be proud of what happens.

09:52.801 --> 09:55.053
I like to be proud
of the whole experience.

09:55.137 --> 09:57.764
I like to know that it smells
sweet, not horrible.

09:57.848 --> 10:03.145
Hold up, hold up.
There are two hot dogs with chili
somewhere in my pant suit.

10:03.187 --> 10:06.064
Why are you always toting
that toothbrush around for?

10:06.148 --> 10:09.359
I'll tell you what.
Why don't you guys try some salad?

10:09.443 --> 10:12.821
- "I have a mixed salad in my bag."
- "Euless, I don't eat at all."

10:12.905 --> 10:15.991
- I don't eat at all.
- And you don't stretch
before you work, either.

10:16.074 --> 10:19.536
When I get a hankering for something
to eat, I chew it and spit it out.

10:19.620 --> 10:21.747
Know what I'm sayin'?

10:23.290 --> 10:27.336
Hey, there's those kids again.
They're trying to steal a car.

10:27.419 --> 10:31.089
No. Excuse me.
You'll not touch that. No.

10:31.173 --> 10:33.509
It's that crazy nigger,
Rico Rice.

10:33.592 --> 10:35.636
You just get off that bike.

10:35.719 --> 10:39.014
My dad's at lunch right now,
but you know what he said he'd do
if he caught you around here again.

10:39.056 --> 10:41.350
I'd like to see him try.

10:41.391 --> 10:45.103
Sonya, excuse me, but you're
already busted for stealin'
Nathan Worthin's car.

10:45.187 --> 10:47.689
If my pop comes out here
shootin' his machine gun,

10:47.773 --> 10:52.152
it ain't gonna be me goin' to federal
prison or sittin' in the electric chair.

10:52.236 --> 10:55.739
- "Shock!"
- This piece of junk ain't doin'
nothin' but sittin' in a ditch.

10:55.822 --> 10:58.200
Well, duh.
I gotta fix the damn thing.

10:58.242 --> 11:00.577
"Well, duh.
I gotta fix the damn thing."

11:00.661 --> 11:03.372
I believe it's on.

11:06.917 --> 11:10.629
Whoo! Now say that to my face,
playboy! Whoo! Burnt bacon!

11:12.381 --> 11:14.758
Come on, get it on!

11:14.842 --> 11:17.803
Break it, break it, break it.
Break it up. Break it up.

11:17.886 --> 11:20.305
- Come on, man!
- You'll get us all fired.

11:20.389 --> 11:24.142
Here's the story. Buddy, George
and Vernon, you can touch the bike.

11:24.226 --> 11:26.395
Sonya, you cannot.

11:28.438 --> 11:31.733
What's happening, Buddy?

11:31.817 --> 11:34.570
- How're you doin'?
Long time no see.
- Yeah.

11:34.653 --> 11:37.197
- How's your moms?
- She doin' all right.

11:37.281 --> 11:40.367
- Yeah?
- Still got trouble
gettin' to sleep at night.

11:40.450 --> 11:42.995
- That's tough, man.
- Yeah.

11:43.078 --> 11:46.790
- She's been through a lot, you know?
- Yeah, but she's okay.

11:46.874 --> 11:50.669
I just gotta sing to her
before she goes to bed at night.

11:50.752 --> 11:54.131
Otherwise, she can't get to sleep.

11:54.214 --> 11:59.678
Kinda stupid, but it don't
bother me. Makes me sleepy too.

11:59.761 --> 12:02.556
What kind of songs you sing to her?

12:02.639 --> 12:06.560
...she likes the theme
to "Blazing Saddles."

12:08.145 --> 12:11.273
- How's your pee?
- How's my what?

12:11.315 --> 12:13.734
Your pee. Your urine.
Is it clear?

12:15.819 --> 12:18.488
Good.
Means you're healthy.

12:19.823 --> 12:21.783
Cool.

12:21.825 --> 12:24.620
- Why are you tryin'
to get pregnant so bad?
- Who's gonna have a baby?

12:24.661 --> 12:27.623
I don't know. I guess
I just wanna be a baby's mama.

12:27.664 --> 12:29.625
- What about Darrian?
- Oh, child, please.

12:29.666 --> 12:32.002
He is too ugly
to be the father of my child.

12:32.085 --> 12:34.630
Let me tell you,
guys ain't nothin'.

12:34.713 --> 12:38.759
They break up with you,
then they beg you to get back,
and then they break up again.

12:38.842 --> 12:41.470
You should've just left them
alone the first time.

12:41.512 --> 12:45.098
I know. It's like if you don't wanna go
with a guy, and you break up with them,

12:45.182 --> 12:48.101
then they beg you to go back
so that they could break up with you.

12:48.185 --> 12:51.313
Then they can go tellin' their friends,
"Oh, yeah, I broke up with this girl."

12:51.355 --> 12:54.733
I don't understand why they go through
all that. They get on my nerves anyway.

12:54.816 --> 12:57.110
I mean, I swear,
my ex boyfriend makes me sick.

12:57.194 --> 13:00.364
He always wanted to argue.
He'd act childish. He's older than me.

13:00.447 --> 13:03.367
Y'all know y'all are not gonna
find nobody in this town...

13:03.450 --> 13:06.453
that's, that's even close
to bein' perfect.

13:06.537 --> 13:09.665
You all gotta get out, go travelin'.

13:09.706 --> 13:13.961
You see Nasia and George
at the park today talking?

13:14.044 --> 13:16.964
Yo, man, what's up with that, yo?

13:17.047 --> 13:20.467
She better not be tryin'
to hurt my feelings,

13:20.551 --> 13:23.470
and she better not
be hookin' up with him.

13:23.554 --> 13:26.974
Man, this is something
that girls do, man.

13:27.057 --> 13:30.435
They try to dump you and then
go with your best friend, yo.

13:30.519 --> 13:34.189
It's just Denise and all them
puttin' words in their head.

13:34.231 --> 13:37.359
She wouldn't be tryin' to talk to me,
yo, 'cause I wouldn't talk back to her.

13:37.442 --> 13:39.486
That's why she's
talkin' to George.

13:39.570 --> 13:42.698
I don't care about the other girls.
I care about Nasia.

13:42.781 --> 13:45.200
I think about her all the time.

13:48.745 --> 13:50.914
What's that?

13:54.251 --> 13:57.129
I dug this up
in the ground yesterday.

13:57.212 --> 13:59.756
Why you do that to it, man?

13:59.840 --> 14:02.634
I don't know. I was bored.

14:02.718 --> 14:06.847
Destructive kind, yo.
Cheer up, man.

14:40.464 --> 14:44.760
Hey, George. You know,
your Uncle D walked out on us today.

14:44.801 --> 14:47.387
That man's crazy.

14:47.471 --> 14:50.557
I swear, Rico's father thought
he was gonna have a conniption fit.

14:50.641 --> 14:53.560
I thought he was gonna bust.
What do you call it? A crazy move?

14:53.644 --> 14:56.647
Nothing shocks my dad, man.
That's why he's the boss,

14:56.730 --> 15:00.150
and that's why he just bought
a K-Car turbo, as in King Car Turbo.

15:00.234 --> 15:02.236
That's right.

15:02.319 --> 15:05.572
- That's a good-lookin' dog.
- He is a nice dog.
Where'd you get him at?

15:05.656 --> 15:07.908
I don't know.
I just found it.

15:07.991 --> 15:11.912
Yeah, I seen a dog like that on
television. Man, that's rare as crap.

15:11.995 --> 15:14.248
Smells like crap.

15:14.331 --> 15:17.626
Have you had that thing
checked out for a hysterectomy?

15:17.668 --> 15:20.629
I think it's got
halitosis or something.

15:20.671 --> 15:23.549
You should give it cold lima beans
with a little bit of salt.

15:23.632 --> 15:25.551
Anyways, are you
gonna keep that puppy?

15:25.634 --> 15:29.847
- No. My uncle won't let me keep a dog.
- Oh, that's right.

15:29.930 --> 15:33.851
Old Damascus would probably cut its head
off or somethin'. He's a crazy man.

15:33.934 --> 15:37.604
I remember this one time we were over at
Barry's house. He was havin' a cookout.

15:37.688 --> 15:40.357
And Barry's cat started
freakin' out, right?

15:40.440 --> 15:44.862
Like he was high, like he
was physically insane, right?

15:44.903 --> 15:48.240
And that cat starts pushin' over
people's drinks, you know,

15:48.323 --> 15:52.161
usin' the restroom everywhere,
and Damascus shows up, right?

15:52.244 --> 15:55.747
And he pulls a whip out
of his, out of his shorts.

15:55.831 --> 15:58.584
That cat runs to the left,
and he pops it to the left,

15:58.667 --> 16:01.336
then he runs to the right
and pops it to the right.

16:01.378 --> 16:05.174
And then he pops that cat like
right on the bridge of its nose,

16:05.215 --> 16:08.635
and that cat rolled over
and started shakin', right?

16:08.719 --> 16:12.347
And it was so gross,
it was like a...

16:12.431 --> 16:17.895
like a dead, old,
gross, dead... squirrel.

16:17.936 --> 16:20.731
Ohh. Excuse me for a second,
would you, please?

16:20.814 --> 16:24.526
I've just had my fruit cup. You're gonna make me vomit,
talkin' about dead squirrels.

16:24.568 --> 16:27.029
No, this...
This is little Bobby.

16:27.070 --> 16:29.406
No, that's
little Bobby's cousin.

16:29.489 --> 16:31.742
- Oh, it's just Richard.
- That ain't no Richard.

16:31.825 --> 16:33.994
- It's Richard.
- Richard might be his middle name.

16:34.077 --> 16:36.455
- It is too Richard.
Look, it's on the back.
- You don't know him.

16:36.538 --> 16:38.999
- Girl, no.
- It's written on the back
of the picture.

16:39.082 --> 16:41.293
Why do you let them
come over here?

16:41.376 --> 16:43.921
Because you know without me
you won't know about things.

16:44.004 --> 16:46.715
Oh, and here comes Vernon.
Look at Vernon.

16:46.798 --> 16:49.551
- Please.
- That boy live here?

16:49.593 --> 16:52.763
- Come in.
- Hey, Vernon, baby, how're you doin'?

16:52.846 --> 16:54.973
- Lookin' good today.
- What's up, y'all?

16:55.057 --> 16:57.100
All you all looking good too.

16:57.184 --> 17:00.187
I know I look good.

17:00.270 --> 17:02.314
Hey, can I speak to Nasia?

17:02.397 --> 17:04.316
No, you don't.

17:04.398 --> 17:07.402
Nasia. Anything you got to say
to her, you can say it to all of us.

17:07.486 --> 17:09.780
- Thank you.
- Shut up. I don't like you anyway.

17:09.863 --> 17:12.491
- No way.
- You don't come in here with that.

17:12.574 --> 17:15.993
You don't come up in my house, dissin'
my friends. What is your function?

17:16.078 --> 17:19.455
- I'm just playin', Nasia.
- What's up with your brother?
Why he ain't call me?

17:19.540 --> 17:22.416
Your brother. What's up with him?

17:22.501 --> 17:25.127
Girl, Denise told me
he ain't had no muscles.

17:25.212 --> 17:27.297
What do you want?

17:27.381 --> 17:30.384
I want to know what's up
with you and Buddy?

17:30.467 --> 17:33.512
What do you mean?
I mean...

17:33.595 --> 17:36.723
You ain't been callin'
him or nothin', man. He told me.

17:36.807 --> 17:40.060
- He said y'all don't even talk no more.
- Yeah, 'cause we broke up.

17:40.143 --> 17:43.647
- Broke up? For what?
- Because he acts too much
like a little kid.

17:43.730 --> 17:46.942
I'm looking
for a more mature person.

17:47.025 --> 17:50.237
Man, he 13, you 12.
Y'all both little kids.

17:50.320 --> 17:52.906
What else y'all
supposed to act like?

17:52.990 --> 17:55.200
He's supposed to act more mature.

17:55.284 --> 17:57.619
But you know what?
I found somebody better.

17:57.703 --> 17:59.621
- Who?
- George.

17:59.705 --> 18:02.708
George?
George is stupid.

18:02.791 --> 18:05.627
His skull ain't even
fused together, man.

18:05.669 --> 18:07.671
He can't even take baths.
He stink.

18:07.713 --> 18:09.756
He wear the same jeans every day.

18:09.840 --> 18:13.177
He don't even talk, man. I think
something wrong with that boy for real.

18:13.260 --> 18:17.264
You know what? This is not
even your problem. Why...

18:17.347 --> 18:19.600
- It is my problem.
- No, it's not.

18:19.683 --> 18:22.769
Yes, it is, because Buddy is like
my little brother, all right?

18:22.853 --> 18:24.897
And I'm just tryin'
to look out for him.

18:24.980 --> 18:29.568
You his first girlfriend.
This is comin' from my heart
right here, you know?

18:29.651 --> 18:33.030
You just tryin' to act like your sister
or somethin', tryin' to be fast.

18:33.113 --> 18:35.407
- "What's wrong with you?"
- You know what?

18:35.490 --> 18:37.659
I don't really care
what you think.

18:37.701 --> 18:40.245
I mean, I like Buddy
up to a certain point.

18:40.329 --> 18:43.832
But you know what? He acts
too much like a little kid,
so I found somebody else.

18:43.916 --> 18:47.336
I don't want him goin' around
goin' crazy because some stupid
little girl dumped him.

18:47.377 --> 18:50.005
I just wanna know why
you two... why you trippin'.

18:51.715 --> 18:54.843
Because he's too young.
Case closed.

18:54.885 --> 18:57.763
I've got people waitin' for me,
so I'll talk to you later.

18:57.846 --> 18:59.765
All right, whatever.

19:41.598 --> 19:44.893
George knew
if his uncle found his dog...

19:44.935 --> 19:46.895
he'd end up killing it...

19:46.937 --> 19:49.773
"'cause he was always killin'stuff"...

19:49.857 --> 19:53.110
bangin'on things and makin'traps.

19:55.779 --> 20:00.325
The dog was very old and lazy...

20:00.409 --> 20:02.369
and just ugly...

20:02.452 --> 20:04.496
but George still loved it.

20:04.580 --> 20:08.584
"It had bumps."
I mean, not bumps.

20:08.667 --> 20:12.713
More like bugs and fleas and ticks.

20:12.796 --> 20:17.092
All kinds of pests,
like, all over its legs.

20:22.931 --> 20:26.018
That I were
as in the months of old,

20:26.101 --> 20:29.438
as in the days
when God watched over me:

20:29.479 --> 20:31.982
When His lamp
shone over my head...

20:32.065 --> 20:35.360
and by His light
I walked through darkness:

20:35.444 --> 20:37.905
When I was in my prime:

20:37.988 --> 20:41.617
When the friendship of God
was upon my tent:

20:41.700 --> 20:44.036
When the Almighty was with me:

20:44.119 --> 20:46.747
When my children were around me:

20:51.668 --> 20:53.879
When my steps
were washed with milk...

20:53.962 --> 20:57.925
and the rock poured out
for me streams of oil.

21:04.681 --> 21:06.892
Hey, is that the Bible
or Shakespeare?

21:11.647 --> 21:15.567
"I mean, they"...
Yes, there are nice people here.

21:15.651 --> 21:19.279
It's a nice town. I mean, it's
like any other place, I guess.

21:19.363 --> 21:23.992
But it's got its good parts, and
then on the other side of the coin,

21:24.034 --> 21:26.537
there are the bad parts too.

21:26.620 --> 21:31.542
But it's really too bad you can't see
the stars on account of all the smoke.

21:31.625 --> 21:35.003
Man, you know what? My room
ain't got no windows anyway.

21:42.052 --> 21:46.014
Hey, man, are you still hanging
out with that girl Nasia?

21:46.098 --> 21:50.352
No, man. She dumped me
last week at church.

21:50.394 --> 21:51.980
What?

21:53.063 --> 21:55.315
- Geez.
- For my friend George Richardson.

21:55.399 --> 21:58.360
It's kind of stupid, though. I mean...

21:58.402 --> 22:01.029
I gave my all to her.

22:01.113 --> 22:04.324
I mean, a plastic ring
and a kiss.

22:04.408 --> 22:06.577
I mean, it's the thought
that counts.

22:06.660 --> 22:08.996
George...
I mean, he's all right.

22:09.079 --> 22:11.957
I mean, if somebody had
to dump you for somebody else,

22:12.040 --> 22:14.918
