54:54.753 --> 54:57.172
I appreciate you comin' by.

55:01.677 --> 55:04.179
I remember a time
I kissed somebody.

55:04.263 --> 55:07.182
I kissed him on the steps.
His name was Charles.

55:07.224 --> 55:09.768
I cannot believe I kissed him.
I just started goin' out with him...

55:09.852 --> 55:12.646
like five minutes before I kissed him.

55:12.688 --> 55:14.773
You're fast, man.

55:14.857 --> 55:17.484
And next thing,
we was on the steps kissin'.

55:17.568 --> 55:19.862
Lord, your cousin
reacted really crazy.

55:19.903 --> 55:22.531
She spit out her soda.
It was terrible.

55:22.614 --> 55:26.160
- She was laughin' at you.
- Yes, then we saw each other
later on that night,

55:26.243 --> 55:29.204
and all we did was kiss,
kiss, kiss, kiss.

55:29.246 --> 55:32.249
That's probably why I don't
like kissin' anymore now.

55:32.332 --> 55:35.586
If somebody
stuck their tongue in my mouth,
I'll have a heart attack. I swear.

55:35.669 --> 55:37.588
I can't stand that.

55:37.671 --> 55:41.466
"Duh Da Nuh Na, a new kind of hero.

55:41.550 --> 55:44.970
"George Richardson,
a 12-year-old New Street resident,

55:45.053 --> 55:48.724
"saved the life of an unidentified
eight-year-old boy yesterday afternoon.

55:48.807 --> 55:53.187
"The youngster had fallen
into the water at the New Main
Street public swimming pool...

55:53.228 --> 55:57.858
"while his mother was having a picnic
with friends at the nearby playground.

55:57.941 --> 56:02.029
"'Carelessness,' the mother blamed.
'It's my own fault.

56:02.070 --> 56:06.241
"'Thank God for giving George
the courage and strength
to be such a hero.

56:06.325 --> 56:09.077
He will always stand in my heart."'

56:09.119 --> 56:13.248
Why'd they put that picture
of me in my drawers?

56:13.332 --> 56:16.418
That's what you were wearing
when they found you.

56:16.502 --> 56:20.255
Oh, yeah. I didn't
want to get my pants wet.

56:20.339 --> 56:23.634
Don't worry about it, baby.
You're the hero.

56:23.717 --> 56:26.261
They'll get your picture
done right one day.

56:32.267 --> 56:35.896
What does the term
"a rolling stone gathers no moss"mean?

56:39.107 --> 56:41.193
If you start something, finish it,

56:41.276 --> 56:44.112
otherwise you'll never
accomplish anything.

56:46.323 --> 56:49.576
- I don't know.
- "Has your life ever been in danger?"

56:49.618 --> 56:52.037
No, ma'am.

56:52.120 --> 56:55.791
One time, my brother got my hand
caught in a bear trap.

56:55.833 --> 56:59.461
There was gushing...
Blood was gushing everywhere,

56:59.545 --> 57:04.299
and we couldn't go to the hospital
'cause we didn't have the money.

57:04.341 --> 57:06.844
So we tried some tape.

57:06.927 --> 57:09.429
When was the last time
you saw Buddy?

57:09.471 --> 57:13.433
About two days
after he disappeared...

57:13.475 --> 57:15.644
before he disappeared, I mean.

57:15.727 --> 57:17.646
And what did he say?

57:17.729 --> 57:20.607
I haven't seen Buddy
in almost six months.

57:20.649 --> 57:23.986
What was the last thing
he said to you?

57:24.069 --> 57:27.573
He said, "See you later, man."

57:29.158 --> 57:33.495
I broke up with Buddy because
I fell in love with another man.

57:56.185 --> 57:59.062
Hey, Daddy,
can I say something?

58:01.982 --> 58:05.652
"I just want to say that"...

58:05.694 --> 58:09.448
You remember when you told me
what happened was an accident,

58:09.531 --> 58:11.617
and I didn't believe you?

58:14.578 --> 58:16.914
Well, I do now.

58:22.878 --> 58:27.299
And I, I love you.

58:27.382 --> 58:31.845
I love you so much,
sometimes I can't even breathe.

01:00:14.990 --> 01:00:18.243
Hey, you wanna get
outta here one weekend?

01:00:18.327 --> 01:00:20.329
You wanna leave?

01:00:20.412 --> 01:00:22.956
You need to get a new shirt.

01:00:38.180 --> 01:00:41.225
Baby, you smell funky.

01:00:41.308 --> 01:00:44.603
You smell good.

01:00:44.686 --> 01:00:48.065
They found Buddy in a peaceful place.

01:00:48.148 --> 01:00:52.027
The water washed... his hands.

01:01:22.766 --> 01:01:27.437
Hi. This is Nasia.
You can talk.

01:01:29.356 --> 01:01:32.943
I don't feel good.
What time is it?

01:01:33.026 --> 01:01:34.945
How's your head?

01:01:35.028 --> 01:01:38.323
I don't know.
It's my stomach.

01:01:38.407 --> 01:01:40.325
You wanna come over
to my house?

01:01:40.409 --> 01:01:43.078
- I wanna see you.
- No.

01:01:43.162 --> 01:01:45.455
I don't think
we should talk anymore.

01:01:45.539 --> 01:01:47.166
Why not?

01:01:48.417 --> 01:01:50.961
I just ain't got nothin' to say.

01:01:57.551 --> 01:02:00.637
George always knew he'd be a hero.

01:02:00.721 --> 01:02:03.432
It's like something
he can sense.

01:02:03.515 --> 01:02:06.018
He can tell
when somebody's in trouble,

01:02:06.101 --> 01:02:10.939
so he's, like, always there,
"trying to help out however he can"...

01:02:13.650 --> 01:02:16.111
walkin'old ladies
across the street,

01:02:16.153 --> 01:02:19.239
teaching kids stuff so they
can walk across the street.

01:02:25.537 --> 01:02:28.999
One time, George saw a dead man
sittin'in a ditch...

01:02:29.082 --> 01:02:31.502
and he brought him
back to life.

01:02:31.585 --> 01:02:33.504
Just little things,

01:02:33.587 --> 01:02:36.465
but they can kind of be bigger
to other people.

01:02:40.594 --> 01:02:43.722
You know, the truth is,
I respect you.

01:02:43.805 --> 01:02:46.141
People might laugh,
but you push on.

01:02:46.225 --> 01:02:50.395
Endurance.
Like a real... athlete.

01:02:52.815 --> 01:02:54.733
"People have two faces"...

01:02:56.276 --> 01:02:59.196
one they have for the crowds,

01:02:59.279 --> 01:03:01.198
one they keep for themselves.

01:03:03.116 --> 01:03:08.622
People might push you down,
but you just gotta get back up...

01:03:08.705 --> 01:03:10.916
and go back to work
the next morning.

01:03:15.379 --> 01:03:18.257
You know,
I saved a man from death once.

01:03:19.341 --> 01:03:22.219
I saved a man from death.

01:03:22.302 --> 01:03:25.514
The truth is, we're all
fightin'for salvation.

01:03:27.266 --> 01:03:29.726
But at the finish line,

01:03:29.810 --> 01:03:32.354
you're probably
a better man than me.

01:03:35.315 --> 01:03:37.734
I'd like to help you...

01:03:41.363 --> 01:03:44.616
if you think I can cut it.

01:04:23.280 --> 01:04:25.908
Get the hell out of here.

01:04:49.556 --> 01:04:52.726
What are you doin'?
What you got your panties on for?

01:04:54.186 --> 01:04:56.104
Just makin' notes.

01:04:58.065 --> 01:05:00.234
That's good.

01:05:00.317 --> 01:05:03.403
The backyard is full of fire
and electrical hazards.

01:05:03.487 --> 01:05:06.782
- I'm just makin' notes of all violations.
- "Oh, yeah?"

01:05:09.576 --> 01:05:11.995
Let me see what else
I can cut up.

01:05:28.971 --> 01:05:31.473
Buddy's ma was a decent woman.

01:05:31.557 --> 01:05:33.809
She didn't ask for no trouble.

01:05:35.978 --> 01:05:38.814
But she would never let
the preacher come inside.

01:05:55.330 --> 01:05:58.792
Too slow.
Go back to bed.

01:06:08.468 --> 01:06:11.847
Damn, you seen George lately?

01:06:13.265 --> 01:06:15.309
Ever since he saved
that little boy,

01:06:15.350 --> 01:06:18.479
he been walkin' around
in this superhero outfit.

01:06:18.562 --> 01:06:21.064
Crazy, man.
He ain't been talkin' to nobody.

01:06:24.693 --> 01:06:29.323
He's been... It's like he
in another world or something.

01:06:29.406 --> 01:06:33.619
Like he above us now since he...
saved that little boy.

01:06:36.872 --> 01:06:40.501
I can't stop thinkin' about
Buddy's mama.

01:06:45.881 --> 01:06:48.217
She was so nice, man.

01:06:48.300 --> 01:06:50.219
She, she don't deserve this.

01:06:51.553 --> 01:06:53.764
I remember one night...

01:06:53.847 --> 01:06:55.766
we ain't had no food in the house.

01:06:57.392 --> 01:06:59.603
So I left...

01:06:59.686 --> 01:07:04.107
and I walked past Buddy's house
and his mama was on the porch.

01:07:04.191 --> 01:07:07.027
And it's like she could feel
that I was hungry.

01:07:08.070 --> 01:07:11.198
So she let me in, and we ate.

01:07:11.281 --> 01:07:13.492
It was, like,
sardines and crackers,

01:07:13.575 --> 01:07:18.705
but... I felt so bad
about eatin' it, man,

01:07:18.747 --> 01:07:22.709
'cause I knew the next day
that they wouldn't have no food.

01:07:22.751 --> 01:07:24.711
They'd go hungry.

01:07:26.296 --> 01:07:29.550
Buddy was so skinny, man.

01:07:31.093 --> 01:07:33.762
And I got all this in reserve.

01:07:33.846 --> 01:07:36.014
I felt so bad about that.

01:07:39.726 --> 01:07:41.645
Can you keep a secret?

01:07:47.151 --> 01:07:51.947
I'm not a good person,
and I don't think nice thoughts.

01:07:53.282 --> 01:07:57.786
Well, we all just a little
screwed up right now.

01:08:02.916 --> 01:08:05.586
But when Buddy died,

01:08:05.627 --> 01:08:08.505
I didn't cry.

01:08:08.589 --> 01:08:10.883
What good is that?

01:08:13.969 --> 01:08:16.388
Well, that's you, Sonya.

01:08:17.473 --> 01:08:20.642
You're like... your brothers, man.

01:08:20.725 --> 01:08:24.188
They don't cry, they don't talk.

01:08:24.270 --> 01:08:27.149
Just go around tearin' up stuff.

01:08:27.191 --> 01:08:30.234
I guess it ain't all that bad.

01:08:30.319 --> 01:08:32.571
I didn't care at all.

01:08:32.654 --> 01:08:34.573
It didn't upset me.

01:08:36.408 --> 01:08:39.912
Vernon, I don't have much
to look forward to.

01:08:41.872 --> 01:08:45.000
I ain't smart. I ain't no good.

01:08:45.082 --> 01:08:47.377
My whole family ain't no good.

01:08:47.461 --> 01:08:50.464
And for the first time in my life,

01:08:50.546 --> 01:08:53.509
I don't got no excuses for my future.

01:09:02.142 --> 01:09:04.603
You can come,
you can come with me, Sonya.

01:09:04.685 --> 01:09:06.604
What if it's contagious?

01:09:08.064 --> 01:09:11.527
What if everybody that touches
me loses what they got?

01:09:12.986 --> 01:09:16.823
I ain't gonna catch it 'cause
I ain't got nothin' to lose.

01:09:24.413 --> 01:09:27.376
Hey, what the hell you doin'?

01:09:27.459 --> 01:09:29.795
Get away from my car!

01:09:33.966 --> 01:09:35.884
Come back here!

01:09:56.238 --> 01:09:58.157
You awake?

01:10:10.419 --> 01:10:16.175
Your sister Whitney told me you
had a dog out back of the house.

01:10:16.258 --> 01:10:21.180
That... it was
a little, ugly dog,

01:10:21.263 --> 01:10:24.183
but that you loved it.

01:10:27.686 --> 01:10:30.105
Do you think I killed your dog?

01:10:34.026 --> 01:10:37.946
All I know is I come around back
of the shed the other night...

01:10:40.616 --> 01:10:43.952
I just hid him in the bushes
and watched him bleed to death.

01:10:46.121 --> 01:10:50.834
Yeah. He was pretty
caught up, huh?

01:10:57.633 --> 01:11:02.721
Look.
I just want you to know...

01:11:05.390 --> 01:11:08.310
...dogs... scare me, okay?

01:11:08.352 --> 01:11:13.315
And dogs...
they really make me nervous.

01:11:16.109 --> 01:11:18.904
You know how...

01:11:18.987 --> 01:11:20.906
dogs play around, right?

01:11:20.989 --> 01:11:23.909
And they'll climb up on your leg...

01:11:23.992 --> 01:11:27.246
and start, you know,
movin' up and down.

01:11:27.329 --> 01:11:30.499
Well, one time...

01:11:30.582 --> 01:11:33.627
I was about...
six years old

01:11:33.710 --> 01:11:35.671
and this dog did that to me.

01:11:35.712 --> 01:11:39.925
And... he knocked me down.

01:11:41.844 --> 01:11:44.346
And he started humpin' me
all over my body.

01:11:48.267 --> 01:11:51.228
It really messed my head up, okay?

01:11:53.814 --> 01:11:57.192
And I wanted so bad...

01:11:58.902 --> 01:12:00.863
to kill this dog.

01:12:00.904 --> 01:12:03.699
I mean, I got a drill,
and I came back lookin' for him.

01:12:03.782 --> 01:12:08.871
And, you know,
he had gone off someplace.

01:12:08.954 --> 01:12:13.208
Someplace special.

01:12:16.961 --> 01:12:19.464
Your dog...

01:12:21.133 --> 01:12:23.051
never had a chance.

01:12:24.678 --> 01:12:26.889
I never gave him a chance.

01:12:26.972 --> 01:12:29.892
I mean,
nobody told me nothin'.

01:12:31.185 --> 01:12:34.813
Okay? I'm sorry.

01:12:37.733 --> 01:12:40.194
I'm sorry, all right?

01:12:42.529 --> 01:12:44.781
All I can say is that...

01:12:48.076 --> 01:12:50.037
I messed up.

01:12:52.331 --> 01:12:56.126
And, all of the sudden,
the only thing...

01:12:57.211 --> 01:13:00.422
that hits me and I'm afraid of...

01:13:00.506 --> 01:13:03.467
is God's judgement.

01:13:12.935 --> 01:13:17.189
- Hey, what's been takin' you so long?
- My mom was yellin' at me.

01:13:17.272 --> 01:13:20.192
Man, some men came by my house
today lookin' for me.

01:13:20.275 --> 01:13:22.194
Man, we gotta get outta here.

01:13:28.617 --> 01:13:30.536
In his heart,

01:13:30.619 --> 01:13:33.580
I think his uncle cared about him.

01:13:33.622 --> 01:13:36.208
He knew George's helmet hurt his head.

01:13:37.751 --> 01:13:40.587
So he made him a soft, new hat...

01:13:40.629 --> 01:13:42.798
out of the skin of his dead dog...

01:13:44.132 --> 01:13:46.093
and an old raccoon's tail.

01:15:29.112 --> 01:15:31.990
George said he wanted to meet
a real hero.

01:15:40.249 --> 01:15:42.626
But I think he just wanted
to walk into that parade...

01:15:42.709 --> 01:15:44.962
and take his place.

01:15:45.045 --> 01:15:47.130
Maybe if no one
would look after him,

01:15:47.214 --> 01:15:49.591
at least they'd look at him.

01:16:12.781 --> 01:16:14.700
Excuse me.

01:16:19.454 --> 01:16:23.125
I just wanted to say
I enjoyed the parade today.

01:16:23.208 --> 01:16:25.460
Thank you very much.

01:16:28.005 --> 01:16:30.465
I thought you were the best part.

01:16:41.768 --> 01:16:44.605
- What you doin'?
- Nothin'.

01:16:45.856 --> 01:16:48.734
- Some people are lookin' for you.
- I don't care.

01:16:59.203 --> 01:17:04.208
You know, there's a place near
the Arctic Circle called Lapland.

01:17:04.291 --> 01:17:06.418
The people there are called Lapps.

01:17:06.502 --> 01:17:10.881
You know, how we're called Americans
'cause we live in America.

01:17:10.964 --> 01:17:14.635
Instead of dogs, you know,
they have reindeer.

01:17:14.718 --> 01:17:16.720
They do a lot of stuff
with the reindeer...

01:17:16.804 --> 01:17:18.806
make clothes out of their fur...

01:17:18.889 --> 01:17:20.849
and they eat their meat too.

01:17:24.561 --> 01:17:26.522
Are you a hero now?

01:17:34.112 --> 01:17:37.324
If I ever get in trouble,
will you save my life?

01:17:40.494 --> 01:17:44.039
Just don't tell nobody my real name.

01:17:44.122 --> 01:17:46.458
I'll tell 'em your name is Jorge.

01:17:46.542 --> 01:17:48.710
That's Spanish for George.

01:17:51.672 --> 01:17:54.299
Sometimes I smile and laugh...

01:17:54.383 --> 01:17:57.719
when I think about all the great
things that you're gonna do.

01:18:02.099 --> 01:18:04.059
I hope you live forever.

01:19:37.528 --> 01:19:40.906
Vernon and Sonya finally stole a car.

01:19:40.989 --> 01:19:43.617
But on their way out of town,
she flipped it...

01:19:43.700 --> 01:19:46.745
and almost killed them both.

01:20:06.974 --> 01:20:08.892
Do you see that?

01:20:20.612 --> 01:20:22.531
What do you see?

01:20:33.250 --> 01:20:36.336
I think the driver was, like,
drinking or something.

01:20:36.378 --> 01:20:40.507
And he drove and fell down.
And then his car got messed up.

01:20:40.591 --> 01:20:44.636
I was on my way to work,
and I just see a lot of smoke
and a lot of blood down here.

01:20:44.720 --> 01:20:48.056
I looked down,
and I seen a car crashing.

01:20:48.098 --> 01:20:50.058
And I hollered out for help.

01:20:50.142 --> 01:20:52.561
Every time I look around, you
and your brother are out somewhere!

01:20:52.603 --> 01:20:54.563
- What are you doing down here?
- I didn't do anything!

01:20:54.605 --> 01:20:57.691
- I saw the smoke blazin', yo. Blood.
- All right.

01:20:57.774 --> 01:21:00.360
First, because
it was going so fast, I guess.

01:21:00.444 --> 01:21:03.906
But you don't see that.
"But, see, what it did"...

01:21:03.989 --> 01:21:08.660
If the car would have
backed up, it would have fell
or at least ran into the pole.

01:21:08.744 --> 01:21:10.787
This is the eighth time
I seen you out here!

01:21:10.871 --> 01:21:14.458
Next time I'm not
gonna keep runnin' out my house,
looking for you and your brother!

01:21:14.541 --> 01:21:17.920
I was just standing at the bus stop, and
I see this smoke coming out of the car.

01:21:19.004 --> 01:21:21.924
- Okay, Momma.
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

01:22:27.489 --> 01:22:29.408
My heroes are...

01:22:30.659 --> 01:22:33.871
the man that invented
the steam shovel,

01:22:33.954 --> 01:22:37.416
Chubby Checker,
the Untouchables,

01:22:38.667 --> 01:22:40.836
Dick Allen,

01:22:40.919 --> 01:22:42.838
World Be Free,

01:22:44.923 --> 01:22:47.468
Great Wall of China,

01:22:47.551 --> 01:22:52.139
Uncle Sam and the president
of the United States of, of America.

01:22:53.515 --> 01:22:56.643
What makes someone a hero?

01:22:56.727 --> 01:22:59.730
I think a hero should be wise,

01:22:59.813 --> 01:23:02.566
strong and very talented.

01:23:04.526 --> 01:23:07.571
They should also have a list...

01:23:07.654 --> 01:23:11.825
of dangerous and poisonous things.

01:23:11.867 --> 01:23:13.827
What makes you a hero, George?

01:23:15.454 --> 01:23:19.166
I'm a hero because...

01:23:19.208 --> 01:23:22.002
I like to save people's lives.

01:23:22.044 --> 01:23:24.004
Stuff like that.

01:23:50.864 --> 01:23:54.868
Hey. Hey, where are the rest
of your friends? They're
gonna miss the fireworks.

01:23:54.952 --> 01:23:57.037
My friends are dead.

01:23:59.331 --> 01:24:01.375
What do you mean, they're dead?
They died?

01:24:01.458 --> 01:24:05.045
They all got killed
in a train wreck.

01:24:10.175 --> 01:24:12.094
Man, that's tough.

01:24:13.679 --> 01:24:16.348
What are you talkin' about?

01:24:18.142 --> 01:24:23.313
All I know is I wanna be the strongest
man in the world sometimes.

01:24:25.607 --> 01:24:27.568
Well, there you go.

01:24:32.281 --> 01:24:37.411
Look at my tongue.

01:24:59.475 --> 01:25:01.935
We all want families who love us...

01:25:01.977 --> 01:25:04.605
because friends go separate ways.

01:25:05.856 --> 01:25:09.067
Some of us know our place,
our home,

01:25:09.151 --> 01:25:11.069
our comfort.

01:25:12.779 --> 01:25:15.407
But for some,
it's not that simple.

01:25:27.920 --> 01:25:31.965
Buddy was just crazy.

01:25:32.049 --> 01:25:34.802
He was playing in,

01:25:34.843 --> 01:25:36.845
in the bathroom one time.

01:25:36.929 --> 01:25:38.847
He slipped.

01:25:44.478 --> 01:25:46.396
My friend George,

01:25:46.480 --> 01:25:48.857
he told me
that he could read God's mind.

01:25:50.234 --> 01:25:53.612
He told me he knew
what God was gonna create,

